{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01NTVAJJNEZ2Kuqi7UbAUeho","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to generate 10 realistic fake OCR recipe text files. Let me break down the requirements:\n\n1. Save to: tools/title-loop/input/{RECIPE_TITLE}.generated.24.txt\n2. Filename rules:\n   - Use SPACES not hyphens/underscores\n   - Preserve Polish diacritics\n   - Filename title must match the main title in content (case-insensitive OK)\n\n3. Recipe mix: ~60% English, ~40% Polish\n4. Variety: soups, mains, desserts, salads, appetizers, breads, drinks, preserves\n5. Multi-word titles (2-5 words) and single-word mix\n\n6. Pattern requirements:\n   - 5 files with MULTILANG: Polish title line 1, English variant line 2, optionally another script line 3\n   - 3 files with COMPOUND: Multiple recipes/variations in one title\n   - 2 files with SIMPLE: Basic OCR noise (stray numbers, page headers, broken words)\n\n7. File length: 15-60 lines, spillover files should be longer (40-60 lines)\n\n8. Don't generate recipes already in the provided list\n\nLet me create 10 distinct recipes:\n\nMULTILANG (5):\n1. Żurawina Tort (Polish/English) - Cranberry Cake\n2. Piernik z Żurawiną (Polish/English) - Gingerbread with Cranberries\n3. Zupa Kapusniak (Polish/English) - Cabbage Soup\n4. Kluski Śląskie ze Szpinakiem (Polish/English) - Silesian Dumplings with Spinach\n5. Sernik ze Śliwkami (Polish/English) - Cheesecake with Plums\n\nCOMPOUND (3):\n6. GRILLED COD WITH LIME + GRILLED COD WITH DILL BUTTER\n\n\n7. POLISH SOUR RYE BREAD : WITH CARAWAY : WITH FENNEL (VARIATION)\n8. WALNUT TART : HAZELNUT TART (VARIATION B)\n\nSIMPLE (2):\n9. Bigos Zimowy - with OCR noise\n10. Apple Strudel - with OCR noise\n\nNow I'll generate these files, starting with the multilang recipes that have Polish titles followed by English variants, then the compound recipes with multiple variations in a single title, and finally the simple recipes with OCR artifacts like stray numbers and broken words scattered throughout. - SIMPLE with noise\n\nI'm organizing these into categories based on their structure and language requirements. The multilingual entries need translations across several languages, while the compound recipes reference multiple related dishes that should be grouped together. The simpler entries with OCR artifacts need cleaning up, and I should handle each file type appropriately based on its complexity.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20743,"cache_read_input_tokens":84762,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":20743},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d60b2f24-f12f-4cee-a7d7-883c82b4ef21","uuid":"cef68ffb-8349-441b-aa39-1ed8be0fc80c"}
