{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KTNyv4eDrah98ySCqrsx4N","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Piernik z Żurawiną.generated.24.txt"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d60b2f24-f12f-4cee-a7d7-883c82b4ef21","uuid":"e1e03dd4-2b9e-4213-ae94-c28288c72e64","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Piernik z Żurawiną.generated.24.txt","content":"Piernik z Żurawiną\nGingerbread with Cranberries\nPains d'épices aux Airelles\n\nSKŁADNIKI:\n\n- 2 cups all-purpose flour\n- 1 teaspoon baking soda\n- 1½ teaspoons baking powder\n- 1½ teaspoons ground ginger\n- 1 teaspoon cinnamon\n- ½ teaspoon ground cloves\n- ¼ teaspoon ground cardamom\n- ½ cup unsalted butter\n- ¾ cup honey\n- ¼ cup molasses\n- 1 egg\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1 cup fresh or frozen cranberries\n- 2 tablespoons flour (for coating cranberries)\n\nINSTRUKCJE PRZYGOTOWANIA:\n\n1. Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease a 9-inch round baking pan.\n\n2. In a small bowl, whisk together flour, baking soda, baking powder, ginger,\n   cinnamon, cloves, and cardamom.\n\n3. In a saucepan, melt butter with honey and molasses over medium heat.\n\n4. Remove from heat and cool slightly. Stir in egg and vanilla extract.\n\n5. Combine wet ingredients with dry ingredients until just blended.\n\n6. Toss cranberries with 2 tablespoons flour and fold into batter.\n\n7. Pour into prepared pan and smooth the top.\n\n8. Bake for 35-40 minutes until a skewer inserted in center comes out clean.\n\n9. Cool in pan for 15 minutes, then turn out onto wire rack.\n\n10. When cooled, serve with whipped cream or crème fraîche.\n\nNOTES: This traditional Polish gingerbread cake develops better flavor after\none day. Store covered at room temperature.","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
