{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Db3ys2iDwqRXAmu6HYDsDg","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Zupa Kapusniak.generated.24.txt"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d60b2f24-f12f-4cee-a7d7-883c82b4ef21","uuid":"4e519199-7678-4a0f-ac9f-2989dc24d20f","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Zupa Kapusniak.generated.24.txt","content":"Zupa Kapusniak\nCabbage and Mushroom Soup\n\nSKŁADNIKI (6 porcji):\n\n- 3 tablespoons butter\n- 1 large onion, chopped\n- 8 oz mushrooms, sliced\n- ½ pound potatoes, diced\n- ½ small head green cabbage, shredded\n- 6 cups beef or vegetable broth\n- 2 bay leaves\n- 1 teaspoon caraway seeds\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 tablespoons sour cream\n- Fresh dill for garnish\n\nPRZYGOTOWANIE:\n\n1. Melt butter in a large pot over medium heat.\n\n2. Add chopped onion and sauté until translucent, about 5 minutes.\n\n3. Add sliced mushrooms and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n\n4. Add diced potatoes and shredded cabbage. Stir well.\n\n5. Pour in broth and add bay leaves and caraway seeds.\n\n6. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 25-30 minutes until\n   vegetables are tender.\n\n7. Season with salt and pepper to taste.\n\n8. Remove bay leaves. Stir in sour cream just before serving.\n\n9. Ladle into bowls and garnish with fresh dill.\n\nSERVING SUGGESTIONS:\nServe hot with rye bread. This soup is even better reheated the next day.\nPairs well with a light salad on the side.\n\nVARIATION:\nAdd 1 cup diced beef or kielbasa for a heartier version.","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
