{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01JWXDNHi5v4ucUYH1N7uHEo","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01SFJRjJhuHmCpAVeeCKH4kq","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Kluski Śląskie ze Szpinakiem.generated.24.txt","content":"Kluski Śląskie ze Szpinakiem\nSilesian Dumplings with Spinach\n\nCIASTO:\n\n- 2 lbs potatoes, peeled and diced\n- 1 cup all-purpose flour\n- 1 egg\n- ½ teaspoon salt\n- ¼ teaspoon white pepper\n- Pinch of nutmeg\n\nNADZIENIE:\n\n- 2 cups fresh spinach, chopped\n- ½ cup caramelized onions\n- ¼ cup grated Gruyère cheese\n- 2 tablespoons butter\n- 1 clove garlic, minced\n- Salt and pepper\n\nPOLEWA:\n\n- 3 tablespoons butter, melted\n- ½ cup panko breadcrumbs, toasted\n- 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped\n- Salt to taste\n\nINSTRUKCJE:\n\n1. Boil potatoes in salted water until very tender. Drain thoroughly.\n\n2. Press potatoes through ricer while still warm into a large bowl.\n\n3. Add flour, egg, salt, pepper, and nutmeg. Mix gently until dough forms.\n\n4. For filling: sauté spinach and garlic in butter until wilted. Mix with\n   caramelized onions and cheese. Cool completely.\n\n5. On a floured surface, divide dough into portions. Flatten each, add 1\n   tablespoon filling in center, and fold into ball.\n\n6. Bring a large pot of salted water to boil. Gently drop dumplings in,\n   working in batches.\n\n7. Dumplings are done when they float and cook for 2 minutes longer.\n\n8. Toss with melted butter, toasted breadcrumbs, and parsley.\n\n9. Serve hot as a main course or side dish.\n\nSERVES 4-6 as a main dish, 8 as a side."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":564,"cache_read_input_tokens":107613,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":564},"output_tokens":6,"service_tier":"standard"