{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01HgHSbyy6VgoEoZCo7wQqYw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01HHtV5qgdEfWLYeijRs4JvP","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Sernik ze Śliwkami.generated.24.txt","content":"Sernik ze Śliwkami\nCheesecake with Plums\nKäsekuchen mit Pflaumen\n\nSPÓD:\n\n- 1½ cups graham cracker crumbs\n- 3 tablespoons granulated sugar\n- 4 tablespoons melted butter\n\nMASA SERNIKOWA:\n\n- 16 oz cream cheese, softened\n- ¾ cup granulated sugar\n- 3 tablespoons cornstarch\n- 3 large eggs, room temperature\n- ⅓ cup sour cream\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- ½ teaspoon lemon zest\n\nWARSTWĘ ŚLIWEK:\n\n- 1 pound fresh plums, halved and pitted\n- 3 tablespoons honey\n- ½ teaspoon cinnamon\n\nPRZYGOTOWANIE:\n\n1. Preheat oven to 325°F. Mix graham cracker crumbs with sugar and melted butter.\n   Press firmly into 9-inch springform pan.\n\n2. Cream softened cheese until smooth. Add sugar mixed with cornstarch.\n\n3. Beat in eggs one at a time, then add sour cream, vanilla, and lemon zest.\n   Mix until just combined.\n\n4. Pour filling over crust. Arrange plum halves cut-side down over top.\n\n5. Drizzle plums with honey and sprinkle with cinnamon.\n\n6. Bake for 50-55 minutes until set but slightly jiggly in center.\n\n7. Turn off oven and crack door open slightly. Let cheesecake cool in oven\n   for 1 hour.\n\n8. Remove from oven and cool completely at room temperature.\n\n9. Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving, preferably overnight.\n\nSERVES 10-12\n\nTIP: For best results, use in-season fresh plums with good flavor."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":658,"cache_read_input_tokens":108177,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":658},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inf